  "prompt": "Complete an orbital diagram for scandium (Sc).?",
  "response": "To complete an orbital diagram for scandium (Sc), we need to follow the rules of electron configuration and the principles of quantum mechanics. Scandium has an atomic number of 21, which means it has 21 electrons. Here\u2019s how we can fill the orbitals:\n\n1. **Understand the order of filling orbitals**: According to the Aufbau principle, electrons fill orbitals starting from the lowest energy level to higher energy levels. The order is as follows:\n   ```\n   1s, 2s, 2p, 3s, 3p, 4s, 3d, 4p, 5s, 4d, 5p, ...\n   ```\n\n2. **Start filling the orbitals**:\n   - **1s orbital**: 2 electrons (1s\u00b2)\n   - **2s orbital**: 2 electrons (2s\u00b2)\n   - **2p orbital**: 6 electrons (2p\u2076)\n   - **3s orbital**: 2 electrons (3s\u00b2)\n   - **3p orbital**: 6 electrons (3p\u2076)\n   - **4s orbital**: 2 electrons (4s\u00b2)\n   - **3d orbital**: 1 electron (3d\u00b9)\n\n3. **Write the electron configuration**:\n   ```\n   1s\u00b2 2s\u00b2 2p\u2076 3s\u00b2 3p\u2076 4s\u00b2 3d\u00b9\n   ```\n\n4. **Draw the orbital diagram**:\n   - Each orbital is represented as a box, and each electron as an arrow pointing up or down to represent its spin.\n   - Here\u2019s how the orbitals are filled:\n\n   ```\n   Orbital: 1s     2s     2p            3s     3p            4s     3d\n   Electrons: \u2191\u2193    \u2191\u2193    \u2191\u2193\u2191\u2193\u2191\u2193        \u2191\u2193    \u2191\u2193\u2191\u2193\u2191\u2193        \u2191\u2193    \u2191\n   ```\n\n5. **Explanation**:\n   - The 1s, 2s, and 3s orbitals are completely filled with 2 electrons each.\n   - The 2p and 3p orbitals are also completely filled with 6 electrons each.\n   - The 4s orbital is filled with 2 electrons.\n   - The 3d orbital has 1 electron, which is the last electron in scandium.\n\nThis orbital diagram and electron configuration correctly represent the distribution of scandium's 21 electrons across its orbitals.",
